  <description><![CDATA[<p>Le Mirabeau Hotel &amp; Spa is a boutique hotel located in the centre of<a data-udi="umb://document/4abc3d9367fc4903a52b296414b05ef1" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4abc3d9367fc4903a52b296414b05ef1}" title="Zermatt"> Zermatt</a> - so you'll only be a short walk away from the resort facilities including the Zermatt railway, bus stop and ski lifts - the Gornegrat and Sunnega lift, making it incredible easy to get onto the slopes each day. The hotel places emphasis on L’art de vivre which is translated from French as the art of living. Here you can expect stylish traditions, fine dining and good wine. To top it off you'll have access to the the indoor pool and Alpine Hideaway Spa during your stay. </p>
<h2>Welcoming hotel team</h2>
<p>The hotel is run by the third generation of the Reichenbach family, whose  grandfather lovingly built the property in 1975.  Since then, the hotel has expanded and has undergone renovations in recent years to create the elegant and chic hotel it is today. The bedrooms are bright, spacious and furnished to a high standard, incorporating traditional Alpine style with modern comforts. Many of the rooms also have balconies with incredible views over Zermatt and the iconic Matterhorn.</p>
<h2>Soothing spa and swimming pool</h2>
<p>After a day of exploring Zermatt there is nowhere better to be than relaxing in the hotels wellness area, the Alpine Hideaway Spa. It's equipped with all the facilities needed to fully relax and revitalise, including a <span>mountain herb-scented sauna or Valaisan wood sauna, a mountain crystal steam room, glacier showers, a jacuzzi and a indoor swimming pool. If you just want to chill out there's also a relaxation room with waterbeds. Treat yourself to a massage or treatment (payable locally) with the in-house therapists while you are away to fully rejuvenate - it's the perfect way to soothe any aches or pains you may have.</span></p>
<h2><span>Mountain meals</span></h2>
<p>After a day of winter activities, enjoy a home made cake and a coffee or hot chocolate in the bar. Each day you can enjoy a delicious evening meal which is influenced by the fresh regional produce, while marvelling at the magnificent views of the Matterhorn. After dinner, relax in <span>front of the fireplace with a cocktail or glass of wine. </span>As well as the fine dining offered, there is also the in-house diner, Marie’s Deli, which was named after the owners great aunt who owned a deli in Zermatt in the 60s. <span>The menu varies between local specialties and comfort food, and is available to dine in or take away, pay locally.</span></p>
<h3>Why is this is an Inghams' Choice property?</h3>
<p><strong>Family run hotel</strong> - Le Mirabeau Hotel &amp; Spa is run by the third generation of the Reichenbach family, who will be sure to make you feel welcome in their hotel.</p>
<p><strong>Unwind and relax</strong> - With fantastic spa facilities and a lovely bar area, the hotel ticks all the boxes for a relaxing winter escape.</p>
<p><strong>Central location</strong> - Located in the centre of Zermatt you can enjoy easy access to the slopes and resort facilities.</p>]]></description>
