  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Standard Twin Rooms</strong> are around 26-35m² and can sleep up to two adults. These stylishly designed rooms have a bath and have a balcony with east or north facing views.</p>
<p><strong>Deluxe Twin Rooms</strong> are around 29m² and sleep two people. These rooms also have a balcony with Matterhorn views.  </p>
<p><strong>North or East Facing Junior Suites</strong> sleep two people and are around 26-29<span>m² and have a balcony overlooking the resort. These rooms are located in the interconnected suites building. These rooms are also located in the interconnected suites building and are on request, please give our Reservations team a call to book this room type.</span></p>
<p><span><strong>Matterhorn View Junior Suites</strong> can sleep up two to three people, with twin beds and an additional sofa bed and are around 35m² and have a balcony. These rooms are also located in the interconnected suites building and are on request, please give our Reservations team a call to book this room type.</span></p>
<p><strong>Alpine Junior Suites </strong>sleep two to three people with a double bed and an additional single sofa bed, these rooms are around 32m². These suites have an open plan bathroom with a rain shower and large bathtub and a balcony. They are located in the interconnected suites building. This room type is on request, please give our Reservations team a call to book this room type.</p>
<p><strong>Standard Single Rooms </strong>are around 20m² and sleep one person and have a balcony with north east views over the resort. These rooms are available on request, please give our Reservations team a call to book this room type.</p>
<p> </p>
